History
1.According to Greek mythology which Gorgon had snakes for hair and could turn onlookers into stone? : Medusa
2.In what year did the French revolution began?: 1789
3.Saint Patrick's Day was originally associated with what color? Blue
4.What island does the statue of liberty stand on? Liberty Island
5.How many Olympic Games have been hosted in Africa?: 0
6.What was the name of the ship on which the Pilgrims travelled to North America in 1620?: Mayflower
7.In which year did French Queen Marie Antoinette go the guillotine? 1793
8.Who killed Kennedy?:Lee Harvey Oswald
9.Which US President gave the famous Gettysburg Address Speech? Abraham Lincoln
10.What name was given to the South African War of 1880-1881? The Boer War.
11.During which war did Florence Nightingale attend to wounded soldiers?Crimean War.
12.What was the name of the legendary sword of King Arthur?:	Excalibur
13.Which notorious 18th Century British pirate wore a beard and became famous for operating around the West Indies and the east coasts of the American colonies? Blackbeard.
14.Which war first introduced the use of tanks? WWI
15.What were Norsemen better known as? Vikings
16.Who was the leader of the Romans when they invaded Great Britain in 55 BC?Julius Caesar.
